chastic variability and high-frequency peaks. This study reveals\nthat short-term optical photometric variability is a very common, if not\nubiquitous, feature intrinsic to the Be optical companions in Be/X-ray\nbinaries. This variability is mainly attributed to pulsations that originate in\nthe stellar interior.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 06:22:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-02"}
