ally drifting and one stationary, which are\nspeculated to be induced at two different sources of the CME-driven shock\nfront. The bidirectional electrons evidenced by series of \"C-shaped\" type III\nbursts suggest that the interchange reconnection be also involved during the\ninteraction of the CME and streamer.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 09:17:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-26"}
