abe theorem to obtain the existence\nof a \\emph{unique probabilistic strong solution}. Finally, we allow both\ndiffusion coefficient $\\mathrm{B}(t,\\cdot)$ and jump noise coefficient\n$\\gamma(t,\\cdot,z)$ to depend on both $\\mathbb{H}$-norm and $\\mathbb{V}$-norm,\nwhich implies that both the coefficients could also depend on the gradient of\nsolution. We establish the global solvability results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 14:04:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-15"}
